i'm using the latest version of express and i stumbled upon a bug. 

Problem:
Express can't find the variables posted to the server with connect.bodyDecoder() enabled.

Steps to reproduce:
1. Build a project skeleton with the express command
2. assigns a routing function to a post request, something like this will do:

   app.post('/', function(req,res){
       res.send(req.param('test'));
   });
3. post a request with a variable called test (content-type set to application/x-www-form-urlencoded)

Result:
Express crashes.

Both ends of the code in the 'connect.methodOverride () connect.bodyDecoder ()' part, what is different?

app.configure(function(){
    app.use(connect.methodOverride());
